modules.description: This module defines configuration parameters for establishing TLS connections, specifically providing a key for client-side TLS configuration. It works with `Tls.Config.client` options to configure secure communication settings. Concrete use cases include setting up client authentication, certificate verification, and protocol versions in TLS-enabled network clients.

This module provides functions to configure TLS connections, including client authentication, certificate verification, and protocol version settings. It operates on `Tls.Config.client` structures to establish secure communication parameters. Use it to set up secure network clients requiring custom TLS policies and credentials.
